    • Field Detail

      • FACE_IMAGE_NAME

        public static final java.lang.String FACE_IMAGE_NAME
        Name of the image sent to MetadataListener that contains face. This image will be sent to MetadataListener during recognition process if showing of face image is enabled (see setShowFaceImage(boolean), and receiving of ImageType.DEWARPED image is enabled with MetadataSettings.ImageMetadataSettings.setDewarpedImageEnabled(boolean)

      • FULL_DOCUMENT_IMAGE

        public static final java.lang.String FULL_DOCUMENT_IMAGE
        Name of the image sent to MetadataListener that contains full document. This image will be sent to MetadataListener during recognition process if displaying of full document image is enabled (see setShowFullDocument(boolean), and receiving of ImageType.DEWARPED image is enabled with MetadataSettings.ImageMetadataSettings.setDewarpedImageEnabled(boolean)

    • Method Detail

      • setShowFullDocument

        public void setShowFullDocument(boolean showFullDocument)
        Set this to true if you use MetadataListener and you want to obtain image containing scanned document. The document image's orientation will be corrected. The reported ImageType will be DEWARPED and image name will be equal to FULL_DOCUMENT_IMAGE. By default, this is turned off. When enabling this, make sure you enabled receiving of dewarped image metadata in MetadataSettings.ImageMetadataSettings.setDewarpedImageEnabled(boolean).
        Parameters:
        showFullDocument - true to obtain image containing scanned document

      • setShowFaceImage

        public void setShowFaceImage(boolean showFaceImage)
        Sets whether face image from ID card should be sent to MetadataListener. If enabled, image will be of type ImageType.DEWARPED, and the name of the image (see Image.getImageName()) will be equal to FACE_IMAGE_NAME, so make sure you subscribe to receiving of ImageType.DEWARPED images with MetadataSettings.ImageMetadataSettings.setDewarpedImageEnabled(boolean)
        Parameters:
        showFaceImage - whether face image should be sent to MetadataListener.

      • setDetectGlare

        public void setDetectGlare(boolean detectGlare)
        Description copied from interface: GlareDetectorOptions
        Defines whether glare detector will be used during recognition process. By default this option is set to true and glare detector is used. If the glare detector is used and obtaining of glare metadata is enabled in MetadataSettings with method MetadataSettings.setGlareMetadataAllowed(boolean), glare status will be reported to MetadataListener. Also when glare is detected OCR will not be performed on the affected document position to prevent errors in the extracted data.
        Specified by:
        setDetectGlare in interface GlareDetectorOptions
        Parameters:
        detectGlare - whether glare detector will be used during recognition process.
